{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, early fusion strategies begin integrating information from different modalities in the initial stages of data processing, such as using LSTM networks to link features of each modality for key sequence information extraction [5,6].",
    "Late fusion, on the other hand, focuses on independently analyzing the intrinsic characteristics of each modality before integrating cross-modal data at the final stage, with the advantage of preserving the independence of each modality's data.",
    "Hybrid fusion methods combine the strengths of both early and late fusion, considering both initial modal information and fully utilizing later data representations, thus showing strong competitiveness in multimodal emotion analysis.",
    "Representation-based approaches emphasize effective representation of modal data before fusion, such as independently extracting features of each modality through pretrained technologies like BERT and the Facial Action Coding System [7].",
    "Pre-trained model methods, like SentiBERT and CM-BERT [8,9], adapt to specific multimodal emotion analysis tasks by fine-tuning large-scale models and datasets."
  ]
}